---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Cigna Global in Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-cigna', text: 'Why Cigna for Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'retiree-considerations', text: 'Retiree Considerations', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Panama', href: '/countries/panama/insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs BUPA', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-bupa-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 55)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Silver', coverage: 'Core inpatient', price: '$280-350/mo' },
  { plan: 'Gold', coverage: 'Inpatient + outpatient', price: '$350-450/mo' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$450-550/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Panama"
  description="Guide to Cigna Global international health insurance for expats and retirees in Panama. Coverage for Hospital Punta Pacífica and medical evacuation."
  headline="Cigna Global in Panama"
  subheadline="Premium international coverage for Panama's retiree community. Strong hospital network and US coverage options."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/panama-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a Cigna Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Cigna Global in Panama</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global is one of the most popular choices among American retirees in Panama. With strong hospital relationships, US coverage options, and comprehensive plans, Cigna addresses the key concerns of Panama's expat community.
  </p>
  <p>
    For retirees who may need care back in the US or want seamless coverage across borders, Cigna's global network and reputation provide peace of mind.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$350-550</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 55)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Direct Billing</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Panama City hospitals</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">US Coverage</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Available option</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Cigna Panama Quote"
    description="Comprehensive coverage for Panama expats and retirees."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-cigna">Why Cigna for Panama</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global stands out for Panama expats for several reasons:
  </p>

  <h3>Hospital Network</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna has relationships with Panama's top private hospitals:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Hospital Punta Pacífica:</strong> Direct billing available at this Johns Hopkins-affiliated facility</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital Nacional:</strong> Part of Cigna's network</li>
    <li><strong>Centro Médico Paitilla:</strong> Established network facility</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>US Coverage Options</h3>
  <p>
    Many American retirees in Panama want the option to return to the US for complex care. Cigna offers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Plans with US coverage included</li>
    <li>Access to US hospital networks</li>
    <li>Coordination with Medicare for those who maintain it</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Retiree-Friendly Features</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Lifetime renewability guarantee</li>
    <li>No upper age limit for new applicants (with medical underwriting)</li>
    <li>Wellness programs designed for older adults</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Pensionado Tip</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      Pensionado visa holders get 20% off medical consultations and 15% off hospital stays in Panama. These discounts apply even when using Cigna, reducing your out-of-pocket costs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 55-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, selected coverage, and deductible.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost Factors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age:</strong> Premiums increase significantly after 60 and 65</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Adding US coverage increases premiums 30-50%</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> Higher deductibles ($2,500-$5,000) can reduce premiums 20-30%</li>
    <li><strong>Area of coverage:</strong> Americas-only is cheaper than worldwide</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics (Gold+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation to nearest appropriate facility</li>
    <li><strong>Cancer treatment:</strong> Full coverage including US facilities</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Covered after waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: 2-year moratorium or underwriting</li>
    <li>Mental health: Limited coverage, varies by plan</li>
    <li>Dental/vision: Optional add-on, limited benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="retiree-considerations">Retiree Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Age-Related Pricing</h3>
  <p>
    Panama's retiree demographic means age-related pricing is especially important:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age 55:</strong> $350-550/month</li>
    <li><strong>Age 65:</strong> $500-800/month</li>
    <li><strong>Age 75:</strong> $700-1,100/month</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Pre-existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    Many retirees have pre-existing conditions. Cigna offers:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Moratorium:</strong> 2-year exclusion, then covered</li>
    <li><strong>Full underwriting:</strong> May cover some conditions immediately, exclude others</li>
    <li><strong>Continuation:</strong> If coming from employer plan, may get better terms</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Living Outside Panama City</h3>
  <p>
    If you live in Boquete, Coronado, or Bocas del Toro, Cigna's evacuation coverage becomes more valuable. You may need transport to Panama City for serious care.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Cigna Plans for Panama"
    description="Find the right coverage level for your needs."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates based on typical scenarios. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your age, health, and coverage needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
